cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE. 

The paper proposes a self-supervised representation learning approach that focuses on maximizing mutual information between features extracted from multiple views of a shared context. The approach is applied to image data and achieves state-of-the-art results on ImageNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses segmentation behavior, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
